APR stands for Annual Percentage Rate. It's a measure used to compare the cost of borrowing or the return on investment across different financial products, such as loans, mortgages, and credit cards. The APR includes not only the interest rate but also any additional fees or costs associated with the loan or credit product, expressed as an annual rate. This makes it easier to compare different financial products on a level playing field.



